        "$:/plugins/Cardo/help/TaskHelp": {
            "text": "@@.help

!!!Tasks are individual items on your To-Do list. 

Put everything you have to do into a series of new tasks, and assign them to appropriate Projects if they are part of a larger set using the ''Project:'' dropdown.

Keep track of your Tasks by status:

:''Next'' - The thing you should immediately focus on, to allow other tasks to progress
:''~WaitingFor'' - Can't complete until something else happens, or delegated to someone else to complete
:''Future'' - A task that doesn't need to happen any time soon, but should get done
:''Dismissed'' - Didn't get done, but worth keeping

{{$:/plugins/Cardo/images/calendar-x}}Next or Waiting tasks can have a due-date set by clicking on the calendar icon. When the date is set and shown, click on the ''[x]'' to clear it.

{{$:/plugins/Cardo/images/context}}Contexts describe the environment best suited to do this task. Sorting by context helps you see everything you need to do while you're //@work//, //@home//, making //@phone// calls, etc.

{{$:/plugins/Cardo/images/checkbox}}When the task is completed, click the checkbox to the left of the task's name.

{{$:/plugins/Cardo/images/star-outline}}If the task is particularly important, click the star.

Using the ''Depends on:'' dropdown, a task can be dependant on another task. For instance, "//Paint the bedroom//" could be dependant on "//Buy paint//"

Use the ''Assigned to:'' and ''Requested by:'' dropdowns to indicate who is responsible for this task, and who asked for it. Tasks will show up in the appropriate person's dashboard.
@@
